<emphasis bold="true" box="[1455,1610,3277,3306]" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Goldman, 1912" authorityName="Goldman" authorityYear="1912" box="[1626,2149,3277,3306]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dariensis">Macrogeomys dariensis Goldman, 1912</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834327" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">“Cana (altitude 2,000 feet), in the mountains of Eastern Panama [= Darien Province].”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[1454,2661,3277,3471]" lastBlockId="16.[709,1303,287,710]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="249" pageId="15" pageNumber="248">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[1768,1935,3356,3385]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrogeomys</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[1953,2119,3356,3385]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Heterogeomys</taxonomicName>
considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[2504,2660,3356,3385]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Orthogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Orthogeomys</taxonomicName>
by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genusstatus by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that FH. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldman" authorityYear="1912" box="[2185,2297,3431,3464]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dariensis">dariensis</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bangs" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[2460,2599,3431,3464]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Orthogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cavator">H. cavator</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Orthogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="249" order="Rodentia" pageId="15" pageNumber="248" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thaeleri">Orthogeomys thaeleri</taxonomicName>
was formerly recognized as a separate species but was synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goldman" authorityYear="1912" box="[811,973,362,395]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="249" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dariensis">H. dariensis</taxonomicName>
by Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
